Preamble

The GNU Affero General Public License is a free, copyleft license for
software and other kinds of works, specifically designed to ensure
freedom with regard to running the program on a network.

If each licensee is to be released from the obligation to share the
source code of a modified version of the program that runs remotely
over a network, then the freedom that the GPL guarantees to users
of the program is not adequate. It is necessary to ensure that
users of such a program have access to the source code of the
modified version even though they may not have received it directly.

This amended Public License applies to any Program which contains
a notice placed by the copyright holder or other authorized party
calling it to be licensed under this License instead of the GNU
General Public License.

The "Program" refers to any distributable program licensed under
this License. The term "cover" means either the Program or a work
based on the Program.

You must make sure that anyone who uses the Program over a network
can download the corresponding source code.

